<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
an enchanter is a lot easier to heal (mana vs hp wise) but he had better not be getting hit that much since it will take up so much mana to keep him/her alive. cast your debuffs always and choose your color stuns wisely that way the mob wont aggro on you so easily. if an enchanter is stunning in turn with a clerics stun and a tank is melleing all the while if there is only one mob like you said then it shouldnt take long for it to die with very little heals necessary. and if there is a secondary healer (druid/shaman) then they can take care of healing the enchanter inbetween the tanks taunting.
</FONT>
