<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Just gathering from this post.  We have a group that we strategically created for grouping.  We have a warrior, Enchanter, Druid, and me the Cleric.  Of course the Warrior is the pure tank.  The Druid tanks a little and buffs.  The Cleric Tanks very little and buffs/heals.  I attack as if I am Death over Time.  I normally don't do DD at all.  Only to help get the final kill on a mob.  The enchanter normally does not stun unless the mob is an spell caster.  The Cleric does the same.  The Enchanter Debuffs and does Crowd control.  Gotta love mez.  We seem to vary our tactics from zone to zone.  Sometimes I can stand in the fray.  Sometimes I have to heal and med, heal and med.  The Enchanter and I always keep an I on each other.  He Mez's anything on me.  So I can get my heals off.  I heal him immediately when damaged(knowing that a couple critical hits in a row could put him away.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
