Norac, yer asking this of clerics so let me explain what I see to be the 2 primary functions of a cleric:<P>1. Keep everyone alive!<P>2. Reduce downtime.<P>So you say you want to color stun. Fine, you get bored and want a more active role. But understand that you're made to be paper thin. Those stuns draw attention on yerself. Mob-taking-a-chunk-out-of-yer-hide attention. Plus yer just running through yer mana chain casting stuns. And sure chain stunning mobs is good preventative damage, but only if it's better efficiency than us throwing out a heal and you saving yer mana fer when it's needed. And besides, what we're looking for is efficiency through lowered downtime. And if you're chain casting, there's a FM cleric and a full health warrior waiting on yer OOM butt. Using yer mana just for mez/debuff works better because say then yer half mana, the clerics half mana from healing and the tanks maybe 3/4 health (ideally, since mana regens faster than hp). Remember, the concern is to stay alive and reduce downtime, raising efficiency. Efficiency ain't a clean an crisp warrior and a out of mana enchanter. Let that warrior take a few hits, long as he lives. He can heal up as you med. And those warriors love their scars. They like ta brag 'bout them.<BR>Oh and by the way this wisdom is coming from a level 9 cleric (highest char). I just realized I'm having ta explain this to a level 49 enchanter. Imagine a level 49 in a group attracting attention to himself from a mob like that. You wonder how many times he gets his group, if not just himself, killed? I can only think o' one way you can't get, 45 levels ago. Ya stink of newbie Norac, Ebay style. How much did ya pay fer the account?<P>Dagis<BR>Midget (Dwarven) Cleric<BR>Tarrew Marr<BR>Stubbornly holding ale to be the one true path to enlightenment.<BR>"Feel the icy wrath of, of....of my ten point heal! Yeah, I know it's not very intimidating, I'm working on it. Bite me."
