Ack, Im almost afraid to post this.  sigh, here goes.  Okay, I am a lvl 40 enchanter atm.  I spent most of my post 29 years in Cazic and Lguk, where there are a lot of mobs that cast spells.  I have used both strategies, pure mez and debuff, and also color stunning.  My experience has been that the group makes all the difference in which strategy works.  If you have a cleric, enchanter and 4 heavy tank classes that tuant, then color is a very effective way to keep casters from frying your group.  If your primary tank is a monk with a rogue backup, then mes is the best way to go, with occasional WTYH thrown in to help the rogue backstab.  If your group is caster heavy, then mes is the ONLY way to go.  So im not sure that color stun is a bad thing, it is just not the only thing.  Part of being an enchanter is being versatile, and thinking on your feet.  this is just my own 2 copper pieces.<P>Briala Mistcaller
