Whether you use color stun or not really depends on the mob you are fighting and how you are pulling.<P>i frequently group with a shaman, enchanter, and two warriors and me the cleric, we usually fill the 6th slot with whom ever is readily available, i might i say we kick butt.<P>the only time our chanter uses color stun, as previously stated was to stop caster mobs, combined with my stuns we can effectively stop any caster from casting.  We usually pull non stop so using color stun over and over on everymob will leave you oom or lom, which hurts the rest of the group when multiple mobs are pulled, or something pops during a pull.<P>usually our chanter will open with tash(duh!) and follow with dots damage shields, augment or similiar atk speed buffs, then if necassary a couple debuffs because are shammy can do debuffing as well, then sometimes just because, he will throw a couple stuns.<P>Now for doing it over and over again until the mobs hits you several times and not the warrior, i really recomend that you do NOT do this, mezzing is a big enough aggro as it is and you are gonna take your fare share of hits trust me =P and the warriors ac are far greater than yours so in total he will take less damage per hit, so its better for us to heal them primarily if we can help it<P>so unless the mob is a caster i would say do not chain cast your color stun, wastes your mana and the clerics mana for healing you, throw a dot or debuff or something instead<P>just my opinon
