To the chanter that posted this post over in the chanter boards.  Ae stuns are very situational.  IE I have 5 inc I single mezz 3, AE stun target and mezz last one.  If you ae stun on more then 2inc with out the tank being almost dead they are all gonna turn to you and then there goes your clerics mana.  However some times It is required to ae stun to try to lock down mezz IE you cleric is getting beat down.  That is when you try to use ae stun to lock down mezz.  The rest of the time just single mezz save the color lines for mobs that ae like the icey's in SG.  Those mobs you will save your clerics mana by stunning and getting hit a bit rather then the icey throwing out 5-9 ae 500 dd's.  However most of the time it is better to let your tank get beat down while you single mezz them.  Thats what CH is for.  If you don't think CH gonna be in time then throw in an ae stun.  <BR>kerbo 60 chanter<BR>rodcet
