the answer to the question asked is that tanks are easier to heal.  large hp are *easier* to heal than small hp.  characters with high ac take damage more slowly than characters with low.  So tanks are easier to heal than chanters in the long run.<P>However, a good chanter can hold an entire camp on ice while a cleric meds.  So even if everyone else in the group dies, I want to keep the chanter alive until the very last.  If necessary, chanter can ice the camp, I med, I rez, and when everyone is up and buffed again, we start into the camp again.<P>If the best tank in the group is low ac, then maybe the stuns would be better.  But in most cases, I suspect that the stuns should be reserved for crowd control and for interrupting casters.<P>Does this shift for other healing classes?  I dunno.  Past about 45, the other healing classes don't really do the job.  Not until the shammy gets their higher level slows, torpor, etc.  Until then, the shammy and druid can't really keep people battle healed for long.  And you'll need to take breaks for them to med.  Using stun to decrease the damage taken might be an ok strategy with them.  I dunno.  I don't play either of those classes.<P>Aidal
</FONT>
