ok ... I am a 55th ( yay ding! ) Enchanter who never gets to group with a cleric ... but yet, surprise!!, I still visit dungeons, and out door zones with minimal problems...<P>Our group usually consists of:<P>Epic wizzy ( 55th )<BR>Paly ( 60th - puller )<BR>Monk ( 55 )<BR>Epic Rogue ( 60th )<BR>Enchanter ( me, 55th no epic )<P>we make our paly pull his weight.  He is a very very skilled paly - I have yet to find a better played paly.  Also, notice we dont have a cleric.  We are still looking for a cleric who likes group and adventure - Will post a post in the Saryrn server.<P>Anyways .. typically, our Paly will pull with a stun type of spell, and usually keeps root memmed for multiple reasons .... 1.) To keep aggro and 2.) when breaking mezz.<P>I usually will have beserker str memmed most of the time ( depends on situation ) so I can cast that on whomever needs it.  It helps the paly get his heals off on himself.  We are all very very good with Aggro management.  <P>I also keep 2 stuns memmed to help stun when the mob is a caster type.<P>Between myself and the Wizzy, we do all the necessary CC that is need.  The wizzy even goes as far as pulling aggro off of me, and onto her to ensure I can get the mezz off.  If necessary, she will root park the mob while I get to it.<P>- Rogue and Monk - obvious .. assist paly, kill fast.<P>My point ... Yes, for the most part, I am the choke point for the group - as the paly usually has C2 on all times and needs little downtime to med .. so I have to maintain CC, Aggro, and Mana management to ensure we can keep a constant pull.<P>So, chain stun???  only when I am getting my butt handed to me ... and its only me there to save myself.  Intellectual Superiority helps a TON when trying to channel through hits.  Iksar Form helps alot for downtime healing as well ... and Boone the monk too.<P>There are ways to fight without a cleric, with a cleric, my mana is always the same as the cleric ... if its not, it will be.<P>Uerien Deadweight<B