Well refering to your question.<P>The Tank is the better mana/Heal ratio over the enchanter.<P>Just so you understand this.<P>You see, at 39th, cleric's get complete heal, and that spell lives up to it's name. At 400 mana a shot, and a 10 cast time, it seems harsh. but it can heal up to 10,000 Hp in one shot. This making it the BEST mana/hp ratio spell in the game.<P>However, that spell is lost when casting on a chanter. Cleric's will use greater, or superior, or one of the Heal over Time spells, to keep you alive.<P>None of these spells are nearly as good as the one hit, full life, spell.<P>So.. to answer your question, keeping a tank alive is more mana efficet then keeping a caster alive.<P>As an added note: I do not think a bunch of cleric's should be telling an Enchanter how to play their class.<P>But that is just me.<P>--------------------<P>Glane<BR>Officer of "a Link", on Veeshan Server<BR>A Guild Devoted to Grouping
